cells, yolk sac develops from hypoblast","Both cavities form simultaneously within the trophoblast layer","Both cavities form from the same layer of extraembryonic mesoderm","Both cavities develop from splitting of the primitive endoderm"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring week two of embryological development, the \u003Cstrong\u003Eamniotic cavity forms within the epiblast cells\u003C/strong\u003E through a process of cavitation. Simultaneously, the \u003Cstrong\u003Eyolk sac develops from the hypoblast\u003C/strong\u003E layer as cells migrate and form the primitive yolk sac.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained as follows:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAmniotic cavity forms within hypoblast cells, yolk sac develops from epiblast\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the reverse of the correct process.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBoth cavities form simultaneously within the trophoblast layer\u003C/strong\u003E - The trophoblast gives rise to placental tissues, not these cavities.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBoth cavities form from the same layer of extraembryonic mesoderm\u003C/strong\u003E - While extraembryonic mesoderm does split to form the chorionic cavity, it is not responsible for forming the amniotic or yolk sacs.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBoth cavities develop from splitting of the primitive endoderm\u003C/strong\u003E - These cavities form from different germ layers, not just the primitive endoderm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The amniotic cavity forms within the epiblast layer during week two of development.","The yolk sac develops from the hypoblast layer during week two of development.","The extraembryonic mesoderm splits to form the chorionic and amniotic cavities."],"references":["Sadler TW. Langman\u0027s Medical Embryology: Wolters Kluwer; 2015.","Muhr J, Arbor TC, Ackerman KM. Embryology, Gastrulation. In: StatPearls [Online]. [Updated 2023 Apr 23]. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK554394/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48273"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15837"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48273","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/48273"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-18T21:17:10+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-18T21:17:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8528"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62823"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4935","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4935"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\u